#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:1 other
msgid "Flexibly Integrate other EC Libraries"
msgstr "灵活集成其他EC库"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:4 other
msgid ""
"There are many excellent libraries in our community that provide either "
"testsuites or optimizer implementations. \\ MetaBOX supports their flexible "
"integration to promote the open-source ecosystem in the community. \\ We "
"provide following two examples to showcase such flexible usage, and hope you"
" users come up with more novel integration ideas."
msgstr ""
"我们的社区中有许多优秀的库，它们提供测试套件或优化器实现。MetaBOX "
"支持它们的灵活集成，以促进社区的开源生态系统。我们提供以下两个示例来展示这种灵活的使用方式，并希望用户能提出更多新颖的集成想法。"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:8 other
msgid "EvoX"
msgstr "EvoX"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:10 other
msgid ""
"[EvoX](https://github.com/EMI-Group/evox) is a distributed GPU-accelerated "
"evolutionary computation framework compatible with PyTorch."
msgstr ""
"[EvoX](https://github.com/EMI-Group/evox) 是一个与 PyTorch 兼容的分布式 GPU 加速进化计算框架。"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:12 other
msgid ""
"See "
"[here](https://github.com/MetaEvo/MetaBox/tree/v2.0.0/src/environment/problem/SOO/NE)"
" to check how we wrap BraxProblem from EvoX into the neuroevolution problem "
"instances. Based on the warpped problem instances, users can easily make "
"their own testsuites in MetaBox-v2 and use the testsuites for training and "
"testing MetaBBO baselines."
msgstr ""
"参见 "
"[此处](https://github.com/MetaEvo/MetaBox/tree/v2.0.0/src/environment/problem/SOO/NE)"
" 了解我们如何将 EvoX 中的 BraxProblem 封装为神经演化问题实例。基于封装的问题实例，用户可以轻松在 MetaBox-v2 "
"中创建自己的测试套件，并使用这些测试套件进行 MetaBBO 基线的训练和测试。"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:14 other
msgid "PyPop7"
msgstr "PyPop7"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:16 other
msgid ""
"[PyPop7](https://github.com/Evolutionary-Intelligence/pypop) is a Python "
"library of POPulation-based OPtimization for single-objective, real-"
"parameter, unconstrained black-box problems. It maintains many BBO baselines"
" that could be used and integrated into MetaBox-v2 for comparison and "
"analysis usages."
msgstr ""
"[PyPop7](https://github.com/Evolutionary-Intelligence/pypop) "
"是一个用于单目标、实参数、无约束黑盒问题的 Python 种群优化库。它维护了许多 BBO 基线，可用于并集成到 MetaBox-v2 "
"中进行比较和分析用途。"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly EC Integrate Libraries.md:18 other
msgid ""
"See "
"[here](https://github.com/MetaEvo/MetaBox/blob/v2.0.0/src/baseline/bbo/shade.py)"
" to check how we warp a PyPop7 optimizer into the BBBO optimizer in "
"MetaBox-v2."
msgstr ""
"参考 "
"[此处](https://github.com/MetaEvo/MetaBox/blob/v2.0.0/src/baseline/bbo/shade.py)"
" 来查看我们如何在 MetaBox-v2 中将一个 PyPop7 优化器包装成 BBBO 优化器。"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:1
msgid "Flexibly Leverage Parallelism"
msgstr "灵活利用并行性"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:2
msgid "1. Training parallelism"
msgstr "1. 训练并行性"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:7
msgid ""
"MetaBox-v2 provides "
"[VecEnv](https://github.com/MetaEvo/MetaBox/tree/v2.0.0/src/environment/parallelenv)"
" to support parallel sampling for the training of MetaBBO. The overall "
"workflow is: trh Trainer will traverse each problem instance in the train "
"split. For each problem instance, \"batch_size\" independent optimization "
"environments are constructed and wrapped into a VecEnv, then VecEnv deploies"
" \"batch_size\" subprocesses to concurrently promote the interactions "
"between these optimization environments and the meta-level policy. Users "
"might want to set larger \"batch_size\" to accelerate the learning process. "
"However, it is better to set an approporiate \"batch_size\" considering the "
"hardware used for the training. If your CPU has 64 cores, \"batch_size\" "
"should be no more than 32 to ensure other processes in this hardware are not"
" blocked. Below we show where to set the \"batch_size\"."
msgstr ""
"MetaBox-v2 提供 "
"[VecEnv](https://github.com/MetaEvo/MetaBox/tree/v2.0.0/src/environment/parallelenv)"
" 来支持 MetaBBO 训练的并行采样。整体工作流如下：trh Trainer 会遍历训练集 split 中的每个问题实例。对于每个问题实例，会构建 "
"\\\"batch_size\\\" 个独立的优化环境，并将它们封装到 VecEnv 中，然后 VecEnv 部署 \\\"batch_size\\\""
" 个子进程来并发促进这些优化环境与元级策略之间的交互。用户可能希望设置更大的 \\\"batch_size\\\" "
"来加速学习过程。然而，考虑到用于训练的硬件，最好设置一个适当的 \\\"batch_size\\\"。如果你的 CPU 有 64 "
"核，\\\"batch_size\\\" 不应超过 32，以确保该硬件上的其他进程不会被阻塞。下面我们展示了如何设置 "
"\\\"batch_size\\\"。"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:35
msgid "2. Testing parallelism"
msgstr "2. 并行测试"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:39
msgid "There are five testing modes. "Serial" mode means we test a baseline on a testsuites in a nested loop:"
msgstr "共有五种测试模式。 “串行”模式意味着我们在嵌套循环中对测试套件进行基线测试："

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:47
msgid ""
"The other four modes are parallel modes using Ray to accelerate the testing "
"process. For example, \"Batch\" mode means we select a batch of problem "
"instances and distribute their currrent runs to different CPU cores:"
msgstr ""
"其他四种模式是使用 Ray 来加速测试过程的并行模式。例如，“Batch”模式意味着我们选择一批问题实例，并将它们的当前运行分配到不同的 CPU 核心："

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:57
msgid ""
"\"Full\" mode means we distribute all combination of problem instances and "
"test runs to different CPU cores (as long as the CPU cores users have are "
"enough)."
msgstr "\\\"Full\"意味着我们将所有问题实例和测试运行的不同组合分配到不同的 CPU 核心（只要用户拥有的 CPU 核心足够）。"

#: ../../source/guide/Gallery/Flexibly Leverage Parallelism.md:65
msgid ""
"Users should select testing modes according to their hardware. Although "
"\"Full\" mode introduce significant acceleration if the CPU cores are "
"enough, it is not the case for trivial users. For other testing modes, see "
"[Config](https://metaboxdoc.readthedocs.io/en/docs/guide/QuickStart/Config.html)."
msgstr ""
"用户应根据其硬件选择测试模式。虽然如果CPU核心足够，“Full”模式可以显著加速，但对于普通用户来说，情况并非如此。其他测试模式请参阅[Config](https://metaboxdoc.readthedocs.io/en/docs/guide/QuickStart/Config.html)。"

