#: ../../source/guide/QuickStart/Core Concept.md:1
msgid "Core Concept"
msgstr "核心概念"

#: ../../source/guide/QuickStart/Core Concept.md:3
msgid ""
"💡 **MetaBox is an all-in-one platform for using and developing the "
"algorithms in Meta-Black-Box Optimization (MetaBBO)**. 💡"
msgstr "💡 **MetaBox 是一个用于使用和开发元黑盒优化（MetaBBO）中的算法的集成平台**。 💡"

#: ../../source/guide/QuickStart/Core Concept.md:5
msgid ""
"MetaBBO, an emerging research direction in recent years, aims to automate "
"the design of BBO algorithms by constructing intelligent agents as "
"replacements for human experts. Its dual-layer architecture synergizes:"
msgstr "MetaBBO，近年来兴起的一个研究方向，旨在通过构建智能体来替代人类专家，自动设计BBO算法。其双层架构协同工作："

#: ../../source/guide/QuickStart/Core Concept.md:7
msgid ""
"Low-level​​: Standard BBO algorithms for solving optimization problems."
msgstr "低级：用于解决优化问题的标准 BBO 算法。"

#: ../../source/guide/QuickStart/Core Concept.md:8
msgid ""
"Meta-level​​: A parameterized AI agent that adjusts low-level algorithms in "
"real-time based on their optimization status info."
msgstr "元级：一个参数化的AI代理，根据其优化状态信息实时调整低级算法。"

#: ../../source/guide/QuickStart/Core Concept.md:14
msgid ""
"In low-level optimization environment, a BBO optimizer  $\\mathcal{A}$  is "
"maintained to optimize a problem  $p$  sampled from distribution  "
"$\\mathcal{P}$ . At each optimization step  $t$ , optimization status "
"features are extracted from the current optimization process (such as "
"population and objective values information). Then in meta-level, an "
"algorithm design policy  $\\pi_{\\theta}$  (with learnable parameters  "
"$\\theta$) outputs a desired design  $\\omega_{i}^{t}$  by  "
"$\\omega_{i}^{t}=\\pi_{\\theta}\\left(s_{i}^{t}\\right)$.  $\\mathcal{A}$  "
"optimizes  $p$  by  $\\omega_{i}^{t}$  for one step. A performance "
"measurement function  $r_{t}$  is used to evaluate the performance gain "
"obtained by this algorithm design decision. Suppose  $T$  optimization steps"
" are allowed for the low-level optimization process, then  $\\pi_{\\theta}$"
"  is meta-trained to maximize a meta-objective formulated as:  $J(\\theta)$ "
"= $E_{p \\in \\mathcal{P}}$ \\[ $\\sum_{t=1}^{T} r_{t}$ \\] , which is "
"expectation of accumulated single step performance gain over all problem "
"instances in  $\\mathcal{P}$. In practice, a training problem set serves as "
"Through meta-learning on target problem distribution, MetaBBO shifts from "
"human-expertise-driven design to data-driven automation, delivering "
"unprecedented generalization power and design efficiency, and the "
"performance exceeds that of traditional BBO."
msgstr ""
"在低级优化环境中，维护一个 BBO 优化器 $\\mathcal{A}$ 来优化从分布 $\\mathcal{P}$ 中采样的一个问题 "
"$p$。在每个优化步骤 $t$，从当前优化过程中提取优化状态特征（例如种群和目标值信息）。然后在元级别，一个算法设计策略 "
"$\\pi_{\\theta}$（具有可学习参数 $\\theta$）通过 "
"$\\omega_{i}^{t}=\\pi_{\\theta}\\left(s_{i}^{t}\\right)$ 输出一个期望设计 "
"$\\omega_{i}^{t}$。$\\mathcal{A}$ 通过 $\\omega_{i}^{t}$ 优化 $p$ "
"一步。使用一个性能测量函数 $r_{t}$ 来评估这个算法设计决策获得的性能提升。假设低级优化过程允许 $T$ 步优化，那么 "
"$\\pi_{\\theta}$ 通过元训练来最大化一个元目标，该元目标定义为： $J(\\theta)$ = $E_{p \\in "
"\\mathcal{P}}$ \\[ $\\sum_{t=1}^{T} r_{t}$ \\] ，这是对所有问题实例在 "
"$\\mathcal{P}$ 中的单步性能提升的期望。在实践中，一个训练问题集作为通过在目标问题分布上进行元学习，MetaBBO "
"从人类专家驱动设计转变为数据驱动自动化，提供前所未有的泛化能力和设计效率，性能超过传统 BBO。"

